st generating metadata, which I haven't done. I'm also considering if the framework needs at least one test file—there's an untracked new file to deal with. Plus, there are concerns about using reflection and ensuring coverage with classes.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering reflection alternatives**\\n\\nI could bypass direct reflection by having a method in my helper class. For example, if I use my `Loadable` class that extends `MemoryProfile` and match patterns, I can assert that the profile's marker equals \\\"loadable\\\" without using `classOf`. This avoids dynamic access concerns, but I'm wondering if using the trait name for assertions is acceptable. There's potential trouble with ensuring class reachability in native contexts, and I need to ensure that direct class references are included at build time. I want to confirm everything is properly included in my tests.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring constructor options**\\n\\nI'm considering adding an explicit constructor to a class that extends `MemoryProfile`. It looks like in Scala 3, a class without parameters automatically has a public no-arg constructor. However, making the constructor explicit with `()` could clarify that it's a no-argument constructor, similar to how `new Class()` operates. In the JVM, both no-parameter and empty parameter list constructors are treated the same, so it seems like using `getConstructor()` will work just fine.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining Scala class construction**\\n\\nI see there’s a public nullary constructor in the class, which is good. But, I might have an issue since Scala's top-level classes don’t allow for a `public` keyword. It seems they are default public, but this could be because my source path is for Scala 3, and the top-level class is marked as `final`, while the test class is in the same file. There seems to be a mismatch with the class names too, but it's fine for native metadata tests without a test run. I’ll keep these things in mind!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented focused coverage for `slick.basic.DatabaseConfig$`.\n\nChanges:\n- Added `tests/src/com.typesafe.slick/slick_3/3.6.1/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_slick/slick_3/DatabaseConfigTest.scala`\n  - Covers object-profile loading via `slick.memory.MemoryProfile$`, reaching:\n    - `ClassLoader#loadClass`\n    - `Class#getField`\n    - `Field#get`\n  - Covers class-profile instantiation via a test `MemoryProfile` implementation, reaching:\n    - `ClassLoader#loadClass`\n    - `Class#getConstructor`\n    - `Constructor#newInstance`\n- Removed scaffold placeholder test:\n  - `tests/src/com.typesafe.slick/slick_3/3.6.1/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_slick/slick_3/Slick_3Test.scala`\n\nI did not run tests, per workflow instructions.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_05412a02d134d88e0169faa31ef4d88193942d5bdaad775aef\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 500, "output": 788, "cacheRead": 29184, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30472, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778033426661, "responseId": "resp_05412a02d134d88e0169faa3131eb48193b610cf5051857014"}}
